title: Led Zeppelin - 1971.09.14 Berkeley, Community Theatre
description:
Led Zeppelin - 1971.09.14 Berkeley, Community Theatre   

Community Theatre, Berkeley, California
Godfatherecords "Berkeley Daze - 2nd Night"

Source: 
Incomplete excellent audience recording. 96 minutes.

Details: 
Suprisingly clear recording taped much close to the stage 
without any distortion! All the instruments are perfectly 
balanced and almost no hiss here.

Tracklist:
disc 1
101 immigrant song
102 heartbreaker
103 since I've been loving you
104 black dog
105 dazed and confused

disc 2
201 stairway to heaven
202 that's the way
203 going to california
204 whole lotta love

Comments: 
The sound on this recording is absolutely fabulous! This is 
all that remains from this show, which is actually most of 
the complete show. The playing is simply wonderful, with 
Jimmy's playing shining through as true musical inspiration, 
especially in his Heartbreaker solo. The whole band is playing 
better than ever, and the wild and long medley is exciting, 
especially with Robert's great vocals
